#geneDefinitionsModal(tabindex="-1", role="dialog", aria-labelledby="myModalLabel", aria-hidden="true").modal.fade
  .modal-dialog
    .modal-content
      .modal-header
        button(type="button", data-dismiss="modal").close
          span(aria-hidden="true") &times;
          span.sr-only Close
        h4#myModalLabel.modal-title Concept Definitions

      .modal-body
        .panel
          .panel-body
            p.lead <span style='background-color:rgb(177, 255, 168);'>Gene</span> concepts include:
            ol(style='margin-left: 8px;').list-unstyled
              li <strong>Genes</strong> – a molecular unit of heredity in an organism, and is usually referred to in biomedical literature by their gene name, gene symbol, or both.
              li <strong>Gene Products</strong> – usually a protein or microRNA that is encoded by the gene and will sometimes have the same name/symbol as the gene.
              p <br>If you suspect an unfamiliar term of being a gene/gene product name or symbol but are unsure, check here: <a href='http://www.genenames.org/' target='_blank'>http://www.genenames.org/</a> or <a href='http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/' target='_blank'>http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/</a> or visit our <a href='http://mark2cure.wikia.com/wiki/Board:Genes_Concept_Help' target='_blank'>new Wikia forum for help</a>

      .modal-footer
        button(type="button", data-dismiss="modal").btn.btn-default Close
